{"metadata": {"synopsis": "Harrison (Charles Grodin), Penny (Alfre Woodard), Julia (Kyra Sedgwick) and Milo (Tom Sizemore) die in 1959 when the bus they are riding crashes. The four continue as ghosts, guardians to the child born at the moment of their deaths. Baby Thomas grows up to be a businessman (Robert Downey Jr.) who has memories of his playmates, but assumes they are products of his youthful imagination. When the ghosts realize they need Thomas' help to move on, they decide to make an appearance once more.", "rating": "55", "genre": "Comedy/Science Fiction & Fantasy", "runtime": "1h 44m", "director": "Ron Underwood", "studio": "UniversalPictures,StampedeEntertainment,AlphavilleFilms", "theater_date": "", "dvd_date": "Nov 30, 2016", "box_office": "$16.4M"}, "reviews": {"reviews": ["I have remained fond of Heart and Souls, despite its annoying power to leave not a dry eye in the house.", "", "", "Nice ensemble fantasy-comedy with Robert Downey.", "", "A terrific cast helps to make less-than terrific material work.", "", "", "", "Sappy and overly sentimental. I still liked it, for some reason.", "", "A touching, sentimental little piece of fluff.", "...will likely leave you smiling throughout.", "Touches your heart and soul.", "A delightful fantasy romp that compels us to consider what one action it would take to make our lives complete.", "", "Another one of those syrupy \"supernatural love\" comedies. Pass.", "", "", ""], "rating": ["", "1/5", "2/5", "3/5", "4/5", "3/5", "2/5", "1/5", "2/5", "3/5", "2/5", "3/5", "3.5/4", "4/5", "", "2/5", "2/5", "2/5", "6/8", "1.5/4"], "fresh": ["fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "fresh", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "fresh", "fresh", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten"], "critic": ["Jeffrey M. Anderson", "Thomas Delapa", "Emanuel Levy", "Steve Crum", "Linda Cook", "Nell Minow", "Carol Cling", "Jules Brenner", "Frank Swietek", "Alex Sandell", "Brandon Judell", "Bob